  "texts": [
    "The potential for Blockchain adoption is there but is currently bottlenecked by scalability.",
    "Another obstacle to the adoption of blockchain is the energy demand and the cost (fees).",
    "Most Blockchain 1.0 (Bitcoin) and 2.0 (Ethereum) come with heavy fees, while Blockchain 3.0 (e.g., IOTA) can have zero fees.",
    "Zero fees are possible because IoT devices can communicate autonomously and send verified messages, enabling full automation of decentralised crypto, and future versions can make nano payments possible.",
    "The main problem with IoT Blockchains is the security of IoT devices."
  ],
